p.span: Due to circumstances dealing with COVID-19, the Department of Education is opening the Summer Food Program to Parents/Guardians for their children. Please take note of the following:
*Any child between the ages of 1-18 can be served.

*These meals are free to your child. No money is deducted from your lunch account.
*Meals will consist of 2 meals a day (Breakfast/Lunch).
*Meals will be delivered to Rudd & Marble Rock by school van at approximately 11:00 outside the public libraries.
*Meals can be picked up at the Rockford School. (Please use back high school cafeteria door only from 11:00-11:30.)
*The first delivery/pick up will be Thursday, March 19th.
*Meal deliveries will be available on Monday and Thursday of each week.
If you would like to receive meals please fill out the google form. The form will be open during the duration of COVID-19. You only need to sign up once. Once you sign up you will remain on the list until meals are done being delivered at the end of four weeks.
